# .repos manifest for ~/ros_gz_ws_lyrical -- the separate source workspace that builds
# ROS 2 Lyrical's `ros_gz` bridge + Gazebo Jetty vendor packages on macOS (not available
# prebuilt for Mac; see README.md's "macOS (Apple Silicon, native)" Reproduction section).
#
# Captured 2026-07-23 directly from the actual built workspace on this session's Mac
# (`git remote get-url origin` + `git rev-parse HEAD` per package under src/), not
# reconstructed from memory -- this is the exact commit each package was built at.
#
# Usage (vcstool):
#   mkdir -p ros_gz_ws_lyrical/src && cd ros_gz_ws_lyrical
#   vcs import src < ../notes/ros_gz_ws_lyrical.repos
#   colcon build --symlink-install --cmake-args -DBUILD_TESTING=OFF -Wno-dev \
#     -DCMAKE_OSX_SYSROOT=/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX.sdk
#
# NOT YET independently re-verified as a clean-checkout build (i.e. this manifest was
# captured from an already-built workspace, not proven by importing it fresh and
# rebuilding from zero) -- treat as the best available record of what was actually used,
# not a guaranteed-reproducible recipe until that's done.
